ger miller bream tales and tactics first edition shipping optionsprices  in stock £ qty item description condition report payment options and related products below first edition first print hardback of bream tales and tactics by john bailey and roger miller and published by the crowood press ltd wiltshire in 88 line illustrations by chris turnbull the book is in very good condition clean blue cloth boards with gilt lettering on spine with minor wear to the illustrated dust jacket which is not price clipped light creasing to the edges internally the pages are clean and tight and there are no tears and no inscriptions there is very slight yellowing to the pages john bailey is an internationally renowned author photographer and presenter of television programmes on angling and natural history one of britains bestknown anglers he has written numerous books roger miller is a regular contributor to the angling press and has written a number of books in conjunction with john bailey in bream  tales and tactics they combine their own wide experience and knowledge of the species with the practical wisdom of a dozen other bream specialists  from match man to record holder the result is a comprehensive guide to angling for this popular and widely distributed fish from large watersupply reservoirs where a single fisherman might catch a dozen doublefigure monsters in one hour session by way of difficult meres where a syndicates total seasons catch might amount to no more than four bream a norfolk lake whose sole surviving specimen  the last of the magnificent seven  broke the british record at 3lb oz dr to the hardfighting fish of small east anglian rivers venues of every type are explored in all their detail tackles and tactics hookbaits and groundbaits swims patrol routes and locations are all fully described but this is no mere how to do it manual the tales of the title make it a book that the reader will reach for as much for pleasure during the contemplative hours of the close season as for guidance on the eve of a breaming session after the off contents includes chapters on techniques meres gravel pits reservoirs estate lakes rivers and the contributors who are john bailey tony bromley mike davison paul dennis graham marsden tony miles roger miller alastair nicholson bill rushmer phil smith peter stone chris turnbull alan wilson and john wilson 4 pages illustrated with black  white and colour photographs and line drawings within the text isbn   7  payment can be made by credit card via nochex secure payment processor for uk  international buyers  no fees we also accept cheques or postal orders in british pounds as well as bank drafts also in british pounds please refer to the statement of delivery below  payment by credit card or by postal order item will be posted within  hours  payment by chequebank draft item will be posted when funds have cleared  combined postage if more than one item is purchased please do not hesitate to get in touch if you have any questions    in stock £ qty john bailey roger miller bream tales and tactics first edition  live please help us narrow down your search all states alabama alaska arizona arkansas california colorado connecticut delaware district of columbia florida georgia hawaii idaho illinois indiana iowa kansas kentucky louisiana maine maryland massachusetts michigan minnesota mississippi missouri montana nebraska nevada new hampshire new jersey new mexico new york north carolina north dakota ohio oklahoma oregon pennsylvania rhode island south carolina south dakota tennessee texas utah vermont virginia washington west virginia wisconsin wyoming im not sure please enter a full name please help us narrow down your search first name please enter first name last name please enter last name people searching made easy  peoplelooker looking to find out about someone find information you may not get on google state alabama alaska arizona arkansas california colorado connecticut delaware district of col